OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FSome drizzly rain across Argyll
OL,6,Fin the morning. Otherwise it will be
OL,7,Fdry with cloud thinning to give some
OL,8,Fsunshine during the afternoon, though
OL,9,Fwestern Argyll will stay cloudier.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA sunny evening for most but
OL,12,Fstill more cloud in the west of
OL,13,FArgyll, this cloud edging east across
OL,14,FArgyll overnight. Glasgow and the
OL,15,Fsouth mainly clear.
OL,16,
OL,17,CThursday:FAnother dry day with some
OL,18,Fgood spells of sunshine, though more
OL,19,Fcloud at times around Mull and Oban,
OL,20,Fand high cloud increasing elsewhere
OL,21,Flater. Very warm.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
